Hello @vineel,

The error in the code you shared is happening because you are typing the `msg` variable as the `UserMessage` type. However, the `ChatCompletionStreamRequest` type defines `messages` as follows:

```ts
//...
  messages: Array<
    | (SystemMessage & { role: "system" })
    | (UserMessage & { role: "user" }) // <-- the definition is here
    | (AssistantMessage & { role: "assistant" })
    | (ToolMessage & { role: "tool" })
  >;
//..
```

So, they **combine** the `UserMessage` type **And**

```ts
// ...
export type UserMessage = {
  content: string | Array<ContentChunk> | null;
  role?: UserMessageRole | undefined;
};
// ...
```

the `{ role: "user" }`, which results in the equivalent of:

```ts
{
  content: string | Array<ContentChunk> | null;
  role: "user";
};
```

So, for you:

> In my app, I need to retrieve a chat from the database, add the latest prompt, and stream an answer back to the browser. I was able to get it working in the old JS client, but I ran into some fetch compatibility problems, so I'm trying to upgrade to the TS client.

I think the issue comes from the fact that the type of your database messages doesn't enforce `{ role: "user" }`. So, you could add it directly to your type by doing one of the following options:

**Option 1**
```ts
  const msg = {
    content: "Who is the best French painter? Answer in one short sentence.",
    role: "user",
  } satisfies UserMessage;

  const result = await mistral.chat.stream({
    model: "mistral-small-latest",
    messages: [msg]
  });
```

**Option 2**
```ts
const result = await mistral.chat.stream({
  model: "mistral-small-latest",
  messages: [
    {
      content: "Who is the best French painter? Answer in one short sentence.",
      role: "user",
    },
  ],
});
```

**Option 3**

```ts
const userMessagesFromDB = [
  "Who is the best French painter? Answer in one short sentence.",
  "What is the capital of France?",
  "What is the capital of Italy?",
  "What is the capital of Spain?",
  "What is the capital of Germany?",
];

const result = await mistral.chat.stream({
  model: "mistral-small-latest",
  messages: messagesFromDB.map((msg) => ({
    content: msg,
    role: "user",
  })),
});
```

